<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4559175>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 5. Meriola macrocephala (Nicolet) comb. nov., genitalia. a, female epigyne ventral view (female AMNH MJR-10); b, same, vulva, dorsal lateral view; c, same, detail of secondary spermatheca, arrows to gland ducts. d, left male palp, prolateral view (MACN-Ar MAI-85, images thanks to Matías Izquierdo); e, same, ventral view; f, same, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: CDR = copulatory duct receptacle, CO = copulatory opening, E = embolus, EH = anterior hood, FD = fertilization duct, LL = lateral lobe, LR = lateral ridge, MF = median field, RTA = retrolateral tibial apophysis, S1 = primary spermatheca, S2 = secondary spermatheca, ST = subtegulum, T = tegulum." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4559175/files/figure.png" .

